@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

        - Rename our XSCRIPTS:NewUser.rexx to XSCRIPTS:NewUser.rexx.old
        - Copy NewUser.rexx to XSCRIPTS:NewUser.rexx

        - Makedir XSCRIPTS:NewUserDoor
        - Copy NewUser to XSCRIPTS:NewUserDoor/NewUser
        - Copy Landen to XSCRIPTS:NewUserDoor/Landen
        - Copy documentation to XSCRIPTS:NewUserDoor/

        - Run Xenolink and log-in as a new user
@ENDNODE

@NODE "11" "11"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

NewUser needs NewUser.rexx to start up. NewUser.rexx will tell NewUser
in which node it must start by writing an environment variable called
ENV:NUNode.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "12" "12"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

NewUser is the main program. It can only be started by the Newuser.rexx.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "13" "13"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

This is the config file for NewUser. It will automatically be created when
you don't have this file by running NewUser. The config file contains values
for colours. You can edit the config file and change the values.

Example:

; Change colours by replacing values 0-F
; 0=BLACK      1=DARK-RED     2=DARK-GREEM  3=BROWN     
; 4=DARK-BLEU  5=DARK-PURPLE  6=DARK-CYANE  7=LIGHT-GRAY
; 8=DARK-GRAY  9=LIGHT-RED    A=LIGHT-GREEN B=YELLOW    
; C=LIGHT-BLUE D=LIGHT-PURPLE E=LIGHT-CYANE F=WHITE     
;
COLOR0=0
COLOR1=1
COLOR2=2
COLOR3=3
COLOR4=4
COLOR5=5
COLOR6=6
COLOR7=7
COLOR8=8
COLOR9=9
COLORA=A
COLORB=B
COLORC=C
COLORD=D
COLORE=E
COLORF=F

Say you want to change the colour LIGHT-RED to LIGHT-BLUE then:
change the values for COLOR9=9 to COLOR9=C
@ENDNODE

@NODE "14" "14"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

Plaatsen. are databases of cities which will be used by NewUser.
When a new user have to fill in his city, he can select it out of the
databases. You need the key-file for this.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "15" "15"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

Landen is database of countries which will be used by NewUser.
When a new user have to fill in his country, he can select it out of the
database.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "16" "16"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

NewUser usage XRoboWriter to write a message to the SYSOP or... if you have
the key-file then to the Sysop's name. This message will remind you that a
new user had logged in. The message contains some info about the new user.
If you do not have XRoboWriter then the program will not write a message.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "17" "17"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

For every new user the NewUser program will write a file to:
XUSERS:(new user name)/.address

Contains:          Address
                   City
                   Zip code
                   Country
                   Telephone number (voice)
                   Telephone number (data)
                   An electronic mail address

Which this file you can contact your new user allways.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "18" "18"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

For every new user the NewUser program will write a file to:
XUSERS:(new user name)/.password

Contains:          Password
@ENDNODE

@NODE "19" "19"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

For every new user the NewUser program will write a file to:
XUSERS:(new user name)/.birthday

Contains:          Birthday
@ENDNODE

@NODE "20" "20"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

For every new user the NewUser program will write a file to:
XUSERS:(new user name)/.computer

Contains:          Computer-type
@ENDNODE

@NODE "21" "21"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

This is a quick log file of all your new user.
For every new user the NewUser program will write a file or add to:
XUSERS:(your bbs name).txt

Example:
                     List Created On: 16 Apr 1997 23:10:27                      

                              New Users On UBS-6.                               

UserName                 Alias                    Location           First Time
------------------------ ------------------------ ------------------ -----------
Micheal Jordan           Rambo                     Amsterdam          16 Apr 1997
Jos Verstappen           The Joker                 Rotterdam          17 Apr 1997
@ENDNODE

@NODE "22" "22"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

This is a quick log file of all your new user. You can use this file for
unvalidated users.
For every new user the NewUser program will write a file or add to:
DOORS:NewUsers/NewUsers.LIST

Example:

Micheal Jordan
Jos Verstappen
@ENDNODE

@NODE "23" "23"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

XMENUTEXT:NewUser.TXT is a menu text. You can welcome your new users
which this text file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "24" "24"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

XMENUTEXT:Register.TXT is a menu text. You can ask the new user if he
wants to register on your bbs which this text file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "25" "25"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

XMENUTEXT:ChangeMenuSet.TXT is a menu text. In this text file you
can put all your menu sets.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "26" "26"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

XMENUTEXT:ChangeEditor.TXT is a menu text. In this text file you
can put all your bbs-text-editors.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "27" "27"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

XMENUTEXT:ChangeProtocol.TXT is a menu text. In this text file you
can put all your protocols
@ENDNODE

@NODE "28" "28"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Using"
@TOC "MAIN"

XMENUTEXT:ChangeComputer.TXT is a menu text. In this text file you
can put all the computer types.
@ENDNODE

